  <body>
    <section id="section_ins_mxv_llb">
      <title>Converting JSON to YAML in Oxygen</title>
      <p><ph keyref="product"/> includes a useful and simple tool for converting JSON files to YAML.
        The <uicontrol>JSON to YAML</uicontrol> action for invoking the tool can be found in the
          <menucascade product="developer editor">
          <uicontrol>Tools</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>JSON Tools</uicontrol>
        </menucascade><menucascade product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">
          <uicontrol>XML Tools</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>JSON Tools</uicontrol>
        </menucascade> menu.</p>
      <p>To convert a JSON document to YAML, follow these steps:</p>
      <ol id="ol_o2q_dxv_llb">
        <li>
          <p>Select the <uicontrol>JSON to YAML</uicontrol> action from the <menucascade
              product="developer editor">
              <uicontrol>Tools</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>JSON Tools</uicontrol>
            </menucascade><menucascade product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">
              <uicontrol>XML Tools</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>JSON Tools</uicontrol>
            </menucascade> menu.</p>
          <p>The <uicontrol>JSON to YAML</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed:</p>
          <p>
            <fig id="fig_p2q_dxv_llb">
              <title>JSON to YAML Dialog Box</title>
              <image href="../img/json-to-yaml.png" id="image_q2q_dxv_llb"/>
            </fig>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li> Choose or enter the <uicontrol>JSON URL</uicontrol> for the document you want to
          convert. </li>
        <li> Choose the path of the <uicontrol>Output file</uicontrol> that will contain the
          resulting YAML document. </li>
        <li>
          <b>[Optional]</b> Select the <uicontrol>Open in Editor</uicontrol> option to open the
          resulting XML document in the main editing pane. </li>
        <li> Click the <uicontrol>Convert</uicontrol> button. </li>
      </ol>
      <p><b>Result:</b> The original JSON document is now converted to a YAML document.</p>
    </section>
